t=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529542\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lfh1665702880070.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lfh1665702880070.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lfh1665702880070.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lfh1665702880070\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Application Shells for Servers\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"lfh1665702880070__application_shells_for_servers_100246\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A server shell defines the behavior of an application server, which is responsible for executing remote components such as server pages and services.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lfh1665702880070__p_d30710e1_d30711e1_d30712e1\">Uniface provides its own application server, the Uniface Server (<span class=\"ph filepath\">userver.aps</span>), which provides generic functionality for executing components, and accessing files and databases. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upi1665702529312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upi1665702529312.html\" title=\"A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications.\">Uniface Server</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lfh1665702880070__p_d30713e1_d30714e1_d30715e1\">However, if you need to provide customized behavior, such as authentication routines for web applications, and batch processing, you can define your own application server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lfh1665702880070__p_d30716e1_d30717e1_d30718e1\">A server shell has application triggers and a library, but no server-specific properties.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"lfh1665702880070__note_w6647ab1b5c11_w6648ab1b5_w6649ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When specifying a server shell on\n      the <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.exe</span> command line, the extension <code class=\"ph codeph\">.aps</code> must be\n      added. This is not required when specifying it on the <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span> command\n      line.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529542\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529542\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Application Shells for Servers Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Application Shells for Servers A server shell defines the behavior of an application server, which is responsible for executing remote components such as server pages and services. Uniface provides its own application server, the Uniface Server ( userver.aps ), which provides generic functionality for executing components, and accessing files and databases. For more information, see Uniface Server . However, if you need to provide customized behavior, such as authentication routines for web applications, and batch processing, you can define your own application server. A server shell has application triggers and a library, but no server-specific properties. Note: When specifying a server shell on the ide.exe command line, the extension .aps must be added. This is not required when specifying it on the uniface.exe command line. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}